In it's simplest form  \showable  applies very minimal styling to the HTML (though lots of classes for
your convenience)  syntax :  \showable{Title text}

This is the text that will show

\endshowable  example :    Title text   This is the text that will show     (function(w,d,u){if(!w.$){w._delayed=true;console.info("Delaying JQuery calls");w.readyQ=[];w.bindReadyQ=[];function p(x,y){if(x=="ready"){w.bindReadyQ.push(y);}else{w.readyQ.push(x);}};var a={ready:p,bind:p};w.$=w.jQuery=function(f){if(f===d||f===u){return a}else{p(f)}}}})(window,document)  
    $(document).ready(function(){
        $("#showablelink0").click(function(e){
            e.preventDefault();
            $("#showable0").toggleClass("showable-hidden");
        });
    });
      html :  When the showable is shown the  showable-hidden  class is removed from the top-level div tag  div class= showable-container showable-hidden  id= showable0 
     div class= showable-inner 
         div class= showable-header  id= showabletitle0 
             a href=  id= showablelink0 Title text /a 
         /div 
         div class= showable-body  id= showablebody0 
             p This is the text that will show /p 
         /div 
     /div  /div  script 
$(document).ready(function(){
    $( #showablelink0 ).click(function(){
        $( #showable0 ).toggleClass( showable-hidden );
        return false;
    });
}); /script

If you put text around the  \showable  tag then it will be included with the title link  syntax :  Click \showable{here} to reveal a secret

If you put text around the \showable tag then it will be included with the title link

\endshowable  example :    Click  here  to reveal a secret   If you put text around the \showable tag then it will be included with the title link     
    $(document).ready(function(){
        $("#showablelink1").click(function(e){
            e.preventDefault();
            $("#showable1").toggleClass("showable-hidden");
        });
    });
      html :  ...
         div class= showable-header  id= showabletitle1 
            Click 
             a href=  id= showablelink1 here /a 
            to reveal a secret
         /div 
...

You can include markdown in the body of the showable  syntax :  \showable{Show me the magic}

* **WOW**: its bold text in a list
* that includes more than one item 

\endshowable  example :    Show me the magic    WOW : its bold text in a list  that includes more than one item       
    $(document).ready(function(){
        $("#showablelink2").click(function(e){
            e.preventDefault();
            $("#showable2").toggleClass("showable-hidden");
        });
    });

You can put showables inside each other.  syntax :  \showable{Hint}{hint} there is more to me inside

You can stack showables inside of me

Click here to see \showable{more} hints

**And what have we here**

\endshowable

\endshowable  example :    Hint  there is more to me inside   You can stack showables inside of me    Click here to see  more  hints   And what have we here     
    $(document).ready(function(){
        $("#showablelink4").click(function(e){
            e.preventDefault();
            $("#showable4").toggleClass("showable-hidden");
        });
    });

    $(document).ready(function(){
        $("#showablelink3").click(function(e){
